Second build pass of the `viz_data` binary's pipeline: turns per-leaf tree positions into axis-grouped structure by attaching children to existing leaf nodes, synthesizing new axis nodes into the tree, and resolving each `Category`'s root children from the same bucketing pass.

`leaves(node_order, reps, markers) -> Vec<Leaf<'a>>` builds the axis-grouping input for every original node: it looks up each key's representative `TypedEntry` in `reps` and silently drops any key missing from `reps` via `filter_map` — no error, no panic, just omission. Each leaf's `position` is computed by `crate::tree::position(key, label)` where `label` comes from `label_for(markers, entry.source.line)`; anything that changes how markers map to source lines changes grouping keys downstream.

`apply_grouping(node_order, nodes, categories, grouped)` is the entry point callers use. It runs three steps in order: (1) `apply_children` copies each key's children list from `grouped.children_of` into the existing `nodes` map, leaving nodes untouched if their key isn't in `children_of`; (2) for every `(axis_key, data)` in `grouped.axes`, it appends a synthetic axis node via `add_axis_node`, pushing `axis_key` onto `node_order` and inserting a new `Node` whose preview fields (`terminal`, `multi_line`, `one_liner`, `children`, `description`, `one_liner_root`) are mirrored from the axis's *first choice's* node (via `mirror_fields`/`Mirror`, defaulting to `Mirror::default()` if the axis has no choices or the first choice isn't in `nodes` yet) — order matters here since axis nodes are added after `apply_children`, so children copied in step 1 aren't visible to `mirror_fields` for other axis nodes added later unless already present; (3) for each `Category`, it looks up `format!("cat:{}", cat.label)` in `grouped.children_of` and overwrites `cat.roots` only if that key exists — if absent, `cat.roots` keeps whatever it held before this call (not cleared). The `"cat:{label}"` key convention must match whatever produces `grouped.children_of` (built in the `axis` module); if that prefix format changes there, category root resolution silently stops working instead of erroring.